#!N 
#!CDarkGreen #!N  #!Rchinla Changing the 
Interactor Layout #!N #!EC #!N #!N When an interactor is created, 
its layout is vertical, that is, the interactor label is placed 
at the top of the interactor. Data Explorer allows you to 
choose between this vertical layout and a horizontal layout. The horizontal 
layout places the label on the left side of interactor. #!N 
#!N To change the layout of the interactor: #!N #!I0 #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N 1. Select the interactor. #!N #!I30 
#!N 2. Click on the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Edit #!EF menu  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Set 
Layout... #!EF option. A cascade menu appears for you to choose 
the layout you desire. #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N 
